Stipagrostis amabilis

   [49167.jpg]
   Authority (Schweick.) De Winter
   Family Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
   Synonyms Aristida amabilis Schweick.
   Common names kalahari dune grass, kalahari couch, duinsteekwiet,
   steekwiet, duinekweek, dune bushman grass, duinriet, duinsteekriet,
   dunen-federgras, n!Tka
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 49167

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is a hardy, shrub-like, tufted grass growing up to 2 m
   tall, forming lax, sprawling to dense, erect tufts. USE: Young fresh,
   juicy shoots utilized by game and livestock. It is sometimes an
   important survival food for humans. Erosion control is a critical
   service provided by this ecologically very important grass. It is a
   very effective sand binder and a successful coloniser of unstable dune
   crests. GROWING PERIOD: Perennial. COMMON NAMES: kalahari dune grass.
   FURTHER INF: It occurs predominantly on the crests of the sand dunes in
   the Kalahari and it is a diagnostic species for the plant community of
   this habitat. In Namibia it is found in the Mixed Tree and Shrub
   Savanna of the southern Kalahari. A very drought-resistant species
   playing a pivotal role in the ecology of the Kalahari sand dunes. It is
   confined to sandy soils including white calcareous sand, pink slightly
   calcareous sand and red non-calcareous sand, where it prefers the loose
   and very loose sands of dune slopes and dune crests in the Kalahari
   duneveld.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
